I"˚#<p>Now more than ever, people are struggling to handle the effects of the Coronavirus pandemic. The effects of COVID-19 on teens and young adults have left many scarred with anxiety, depression, or other mental health issues.
Reports of students‚Äô mental health declining pre-pandemic when paired with isolation, switches to online learning, and country-wide social upheaval led many to seek out mental health services to help them cope.</p>

